# Auto-correlation Distance Analysis Script

## Overview
This Perl script calculates the distance distribution between genomic positions from two input files. It computes how frequently positions occur at specific distances from each other (auto-correlation analysis), which is useful for analyzing spatial patterns in genomic features like nucleosome positions or transcription factor binding sites.

## Usage

```bash
perl auto_correlation_multiple_new4_corrected_new.pl <input1> <input2> <output>
```

## Arguments

- `<input1>`: First tab-delimited input file containing genomic positions
- `<input2>`: Second tab-delimited input file containing genomic positions  
- `<output>`: Output file for distance distribution results

## Input File Format

Both input files should be tab-delimited with at least 3 columns:
